            "answer_text": "IT\u2019s not dependent on US tech. Huawei was using US made chips to help balance the trade deficit. Since the US doesn\u2019t want to sell chips to Huawei, Huawei will use Chinese made chips instead. For instance. FPGAs were purchased from Xilinx. Now they will use Gowin FPGAs. They were using memory chips from Micron, now they will use Tsinghua memory. They are producing DDR4 at 19nm. Nand is at 128 layers just like samsung and Micron. Thanks to Trump, China will increase it\u2019s GPD greatly in the next several years due to US losses in chip sales. ",
